Here's the ruthlessly concise material summary of the ASX announcement:

  • Drilling Update at Chancho al Palo (100% Solis):
  • First drill hole (713m depth) intersected IOCG-style mineralisation (184m) and porphyry-style mineralisation (451m+), including visible chalcopyrite and gold.
  • Assays expected July/August 2025.
  • Second drill hole planned ~200m west of first.

  • Total programme: 2,500m (4-5 holes).

  • Visual Estimates (Subject to Assay Confirmation):

  • 184.20-184.75m: 0-0.5% Cu (IOCG breccia).
  • 619.90m: 0.1 g/t Au (visible gold).

  • 520m: 0.3% Cu (disseminated chalcopyrite).

  • Next Steps: Rig mobilisation to Ilo Este after Chancho al Palo completion.

No material financial or capital structure impacts disclosed. Focus remains on exploration results pending assays.

Material Information Summary

  • Exclusive Collaboration Agreement signed with Long Grove Pharmaceuticals (US) for AK-FLOUR® (fluorescein sodium contrast agent), critical for Optiscan’s InVue® surgical imaging device.

  • Develop new clinical applications for AK-FLOUR® in combination with Optiscan’s technology.
  • Support US FDA regulatory submissions for InVue® (initial focus: breast surgery, expanding to GI/robotic/laparoscopic applications).

  • Strategic impact: Strengthens Optiscan’s regulatory pathway and potential commercial reach in the US surgical imaging market.

Financial Highlights

  • Revenue: $17.3bn (+8.9% YoY) or $19.5bn (+7.2%) including charge-through sales.
  • Underlying EBIT: $507.8m (+2.3%).
  • Underlying NPAT: $275.5m (-2.4%).
  • Statutory NPAT: $283.3m (+10.1%).
  • EPS: Underlying 25.1 cps, Statutory 25.9 cps.
  • Operating Cashflow: $539m (+11.7%).

  • Dividend: Final 9.5 cps (fully franked), FY25 total 18.0 cps (72% payout ratio).

Segment Performance

  • Revenue +11.1% ($10.6bn including tobacco).
  • Underlying EBIT +18% (ex-tobacco).
  • Acquisitions (Superior Foods) performing in line.
  • Liquor:
  • Revenue +3.4% ($5.3bn).
  • EBIT -4.7% ($104.1m) due to lower wholesale inflation impacting margins.
  • Market share gains (+270bps since FY22).
  • Hardware:
  • Revenue +2.4% ($3.6bn).
  • EBIT -10.2% ($189.3m) on subdued trade activity and higher depreciation.
  • Improvement in 2H and positive start to FY26.

Strategic & Operational Updates

  • Superior Foods merged with Campbells & Convenience into Foodservice and Convenience.
  • Acquisitions:
  • Announced purchase of Steve’s Liquor Warehouse (8 stores in VIC/TAS).
  • Outlook:
  • FY26 7-week Group revenue +4.7% (ex-Superior Foods +2.7%).
  • Hardware trade sales improving; Liquor market share gains continuing.

Dividend & Capital Management
